      "blocks": {
        "faq_item_Xa7a9G": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "faq_question": "1. What is a Portuguese Cut Diamond?",
            "faq_answer": "<p>A Portuguese Cut Diamond is a rare diamond design featuring 161 to 200 facets, known for its exceptional brilliance and depth. Its intricate faceting creates a unique play of light that’s deeper than most traditional cuts.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_item_rcaANV": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "faq_question": "2. How is a Portuguese Cut Diamond different from a Round Brilliant?",
            "faq_answer": "<p> The Portuguese Cut Diamond vs Round Brilliant comparison shows that the Portuguese cut has more facets and a deeper pavilion, resulting in more fire and dimension, while the Round Brilliant offers a more uniform sparkle.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_item_HMGtjz": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "faq_question": "3. Are Lab Grown Portuguese Cut Diamonds real diamonds?",
            "faq_answer": "<p>Yes. Lab Grown Portuguese Cut Diamonds have the same physical, chemical, and optical properties as mined diamonds — the only difference is that they’re created sustainably in advanced laboratories.<br/><br/></p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_item_UHKzLJ": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "faq_question": "4. Why are Portuguese Cut Diamonds considered rare?",
            "faq_answer": "<p> They are rare because their complex faceting requires expert craftsmanship and precision, making them less commonly produced than modern diamond cuts.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_item_eAdDeB": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "faq_question": "5. What makes a Portuguese Cut Diamond Ring special?",
            "faq_answer": "<p>A Portuguese Cut Diamond Ring combines vintage artistry with modern elegance, offering unmatched brilliance and character — perfect for those seeking a distinctive engagement or heirloom piece.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_item_jktigb": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "disabled": true,
          "settings": {
            "faq_question": "6. Can I get a certification for a lab-grown diamond?",
            "faq_answer": "<p>Yes. Lab-grown diamonds are graded and certified by reputable organizations such as IGI and GIA, providing assurance of quality, authenticity, and ethical sourcing.<br/></p>"
          }
        }
      },
